Package lab.util.commands

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Executable
    This interface should be implemented by any class which is a command.
    Loggable
    This interface should be implemented by any class which needs to log data about execution of its method.
    Packable
    This interface should be implemented by any class of command which can pack its fields.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Add
    This command allows to add new location in collection.
    AddIfMax
    This command allows to add new location in collection if it is more items than each other location in collection.
    ClientCommand
    This class is a base of all client commands classes.
    Command
    Command class is a main class of all commands classes.
    Commands
    Commands class contains static methods to receive commands classes and supported methods for them.
    DBCommand
    This class is a base of all server commands classes which can work with database.
    Exit
    This command allows to exit from client program.
    Get
    This command allows to get all locations from database on server
    Help
    This command allows to receive description of program client side work.
    Import
    This command allows to add new locations in collection from specified file that contains serializable locations in xml format.
    Info
    This command allows to receive about collection on server.
    Login
    This command allows to login into objects system.
    Register
    This command allows to register new user.
    Remove
    This command allows to remove specified location from collection on server if user is an owner of specified object and specified object exists.
    RemoveGreater
    This command allows to remove all locations from collection on server which has more items than specified location.
    RemoveLower
    This command allows to remove all locations from collection on server which has less items than specified location.
    ServerCommand
    This class is a base of all server commands classes.
    Show
    This command allows to show all objects that contains collection on server.
    Subscribe
    This command allows to receive port of server publisher thread that sends changes in collection to its subscribers.
    Update
    This command allows to update location on server if user is an owner of this location.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Commands.CommandExecutionStatus
    Enum of commands execution statuses.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InvalidArgumentsException
    Exception that throws when command and its arguments can't be parsed
